Citation.sTitle: Density, Refractive Index and Volumetric Properties of Water-Ionic Liquid Binary Systems with Imidazolium-Based Cations and Tetrafluoroborate, Triflate and Octylsulfate Anions at T = 293 to 343 K and p = 0.1 MPa
Citation.sAbstract: The density and refractive index of ionic liquids (ILs) + water binary mixtures were determined as a function of temperature (from 293.15 to 343.15 K) at atmospheric pressure over the whole composition range in which the mixtures were miscible. To carry out a systematic study, all the ILs selected are imidazolium-based ILs with a different number of carbons in the alkyl chain of the cation and also different anions (tetrafluoroborate, triflate and octylsulphate).
